<TITLE> Sheikh Selim attends his mother's last rites </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com) Awami League presidium member Sheikh Selim has been freed on parole from 10am till 5pm Friday to enable him to attend the last funeral prayers and burial of his mother. Deputy inspector general (prisons) Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com the former minister was taken from the jail to his Banani home at 10:17am. A bdnews24.com correspondent present there said AL chief and Selim's cousin Sheikh Hasina reached his home at 10:38am. Workers' Party president Rashed Khan Mennon, AL presidium member Matia Chowdhury and AL joint secretary Mukul Bose were present there solacing the bereaved family. Selim's Banani home is secured by the police, with no one except the family relations and political leaders being allowed in. Selim will be taken back to jail at 5pm after he observes the last rites of his deceased mother, said Siddiqui. The DIG prisons said one is not allowed to travel outside the metropolitan area on parole. Earlier, Selim was taken back to jail after more than two hours on parole to see his deceased mother Thursday. Selim's family members waved him a tearful goodnight from the balcony of their house in Banani as a prison van sped him away to the Dhaka Central Jail. Selim waved them back. Achhiya Khatun, also elder sister of independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman and aunt of former prime minister Sheikh Hasina, died of old-age complications at age 90 at ZH Sikder Medical College Hospital in Gulshan Thursday. bdnews24.com/a
